er of them have reached feature lockdown stage as far as I know. One thing to consider is that SoE has a lot of existing code to reuse. For example they can probably lift a large part of the network code straight from EQ (which would be great since its the best network code I have seen in a MMORPG).<br>
<br>
If Blizzard release on schedule summer 2004 I think SoE has a good chance of getting EQ2 out before that. Personally I don't really mind a few bugs at release as long as the game is fun. Just look at EQ and UO. Both had quite a lot of bugs initially. They were still amazing to play though.<br>
