<br>
The Luclin models are a great case in point.  Does anyone think those are as good as they could have been?  It's obvious to me looking at them that all the production time went into one race's model, they discovered they were running out of time, and they copied that race and made slight modifications to make the others.  This is why everyone kneels instead of sits, swims stupidly, stands in awkward postures, why the combat animations are pure ass, etc.  Because they promised the moon on time and instead delivered some stinky cheese!<br>
<br>
I really want EQ2 to be a great game.  I hope SOE takes the time necessary to acheive that, even if that means pushing back the release date.  I can respect that much more than i respect meeting a deadline with crappy content. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=northyr>NOR Thyr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/10/03 7:40 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Given what I've seen of the betas of other SOE games..I can say that if it hasn't started beta yet, the release date of Q4 03 is gonna be pushed back.  Probably a good long ways.  Take SWG for example..everyone's been clamoring for it, it's in Beta 3 (Final Beta as far as I know) and I figure it'll be lucky to get released for Xmas.  <br>
