I really, sincerely hope that they put proper time and effort into giving this game a LONG and THOROUGH beta test.  SOE has built it's entire presence in the MMORPG industry on the strength of Everquest and it'd be dissappointing to see EQ2 ruin that. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=614716">Thyrbit Firefrog</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whizbangdustyboots>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Arcanist<BR>Gnomus Originalus</span><br>  Posts: 13278<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/10/03 8:44 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Stability isnt that indicative at this stage either since neither of them have reached feature lockdown stage as far as I know.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->And the build they created for E3 -- you create special ones, you know, that won't crash the system and show off the cool stuff -- barely worked when they were giving a filmed demonstration for one of the biggest EQ sites.<br>
